{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":800,"text":"So I've been \"futuring,\"\nwhich is a term I made up --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":4200,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":5480,"text":"about three seconds ago."},{"time":6720,"text":"I've been futuring for about 20 years,"},{"time":9560,"text":"and when I first started,\nI would sit down with people,"},{"time":12920,"text":"and say, \"Hey,\nlet's talk 10, 20 years out.\""},{"time":15840,"text":"And they'd say, \"Great.\""},{"time":17640,"text":"And I've been seeing that time horizon"},{"time":20160,"text":"get shorter and shorter"},{"time":22240,"text":"and shorter,"},{"time":23880,"text":"so much so that I met\nwith a CEO two months ago"},{"time":27280,"text":"and I said -- we started\nour initial conversation."},{"time":29680,"text":"He goes, \"I love what you do.\nI want to talk about the next six months.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":33440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":36040,"text":"We have a lot of problems\nthat we are facing."},{"time":39200,"text":"These are civilizational-scale problems."},{"time":43520,"text":"The issue though is,"},{"time":45600,"text":"we can't solve them"},{"time":47320,"text":"using the mental models\nthat we use right now"},{"time":49920,"text":"to try and solve these problems."},{"time":51520,"text":"Yes, a lot of great\ntechnical work is being done,"},{"time":54200,"text":"but there is a problem that\nwe need to solve for a priori, before,"},{"time":59600,"text":"if we want to really\nmove the needle on those big problems."},{"time":63160,"text":"\"Short-termism.\""},{"time":64920,"text":"Right? There's no marches.\nThere's no bracelets."},{"time":67400,"text":"There's no petitions that you can sign\nto be against short-termism."},{"time":71280,"text":"I tried to put one up, and no one signed."},{"time":74120,"text":"It was weird."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75360,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":77280,"text":"But it prevents us from doing so much."},{"time":80320,"text":"Short-termism, for many reasons,"},{"time":83040,"text":"has pervaded every\nnook and cranny of our reality."},{"time":85960,"text":"I just want you to take a second"},{"time":87560,"text":"and just think about an issue\nthat you're thinking, working on."},{"time":91400,"text":"It could be personal, it could be at work"},{"time":93400,"text":"or it could be\nmove-the-needle world stuff,"},{"time":95480,"text":"and think about\nhow far out you tend to think"},{"time":97840,"text":"about the solution set for that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101920,"text":"Because short-termism prevents the CEO"},{"time":106360,"text":"from buying really\nexpensive safety equipment."},{"time":109920,"text":"It'll hurt the bottom line."},{"time":111920,"text":"So we get the Deepwater Horizon."},{"time":114400,"text":"Short-termism prevents teachers"},{"time":117160,"text":"from spending quality\none-on-one time with their students."},{"time":120720,"text":"So right now in America,"},{"time":122880,"text":"a high school student\ndrops out every 26 seconds."},{"time":127360,"text":"Short-termism prevents Congress --"},{"time":130120,"text":"sorry if there's anyone\nin here from Congress --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":132760,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":134320,"text":"or not really that sorry --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":136400,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":138640,"text":"from putting money\ninto a real infrastructure bill."},{"time":141840,"text":"So what we get\nis the I-35W bridge collapse"},{"time":144480,"text":"over the Mississippi a few years ago,"},{"time":146320,"text":"13 killed."},{"time":148760,"text":"It wasn't always like this.\nWe did the Panama Canal."},{"time":152600,"text":"We pretty much\nhave eradicated global polio."},{"time":154880,"text":"We did the transcontinental railroad,\nthe Marshall Plan."},{"time":158560,"text":"And it's not just big, physical\ninfrastructure problems and issues."},{"time":162920,"text":"Women's suffrage, the right to vote."},{"time":164840,"text":"But in our short-termist time,"},{"time":167640,"text":"where everything seems to happen right now"},{"time":170160,"text":"and we can only think out\npast the next tweet or timeline post,"},{"time":174680,"text":"we get hyper-reactionary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176720,"text":"So what do we do?"},{"time":178880,"text":"We take people who are fleeing\ntheir war-torn country,"},{"time":182160,"text":"and we go after them."},{"time":183440,"text":"We take low-level drug offenders,\nand we put them away for life."},{"time":187080,"text":"And then we build McMansions\nwithout even thinking"},{"time":189480,"text":"about how people are going\nto get between them and their job."},{"time":192370,"text":"It's a quick buck."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194760,"text":"Now, the reality is,\nfor a lot of these problems,"},{"time":197120,"text":"there are some technical fixes,"},{"time":199920,"text":"a lot of them."},{"time":201160,"text":"I call these technical fixes\nsandbag strategies."},{"time":204720,"text":"So you know there's a storm coming,"},{"time":206440,"text":"the levee is broken,\nno one's put any money into it,"},{"time":209200,"text":"you surround your home with sandbags."},{"time":211040,"text":"And guess what? It works."},{"time":214600,"text":"Storm goes away,\nthe water level goes down,"},{"time":216640,"text":"you get rid of the sandbags,"},{"time":218040,"text":"and you do this storm\nafter storm after storm."},{"time":221920,"text":"And here's the insidious thing."},{"time":224120,"text":"A sandbag strategy"},{"time":226040,"text":"can get you reelected."},{"time":228320,"text":"A sandbag strategy"},{"time":229720,"text":"can help you make your quarterly numbers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234240,"text":"Now, if we want to move forward"},{"time":237240,"text":"into a different future\nthan the one we have right now,"},{"time":240040,"text":"because I don't think we've hit --"},{"time":242120,"text":"2016 is not peak civilization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":245480,"text":"There's some more we can do."},{"time":247280,"text":"But my argument is that unless we shift\nour mental models and our mental maps"},{"time":251920,"text":"on how we think about the short,"},{"time":254280,"text":"it's not going to happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256000,"text":"So what I've developed\nis something called \"longpath,\""},{"time":259000,"text":"and it's a practice."},{"time":260760,"text":"And longpath isn't\na kind of one-and-done exercise."},{"time":264720,"text":"I'm sure everyone here\nat some point has done an off-site"},{"time":267440,"text":"with a lot of Post-It notes\nand whiteboards,"},{"time":269560,"text":"and you do --"},{"time":272480,"text":"no offense to the consultants\nin here who do that --"},{"time":274960,"text":"and you do a long-term plan,"},{"time":276600,"text":"and then two weeks later,\neveryone forgets about it."},{"time":280640,"text":"Right? Or a week later.\nIf you're lucky, three months."},{"time":284840,"text":"It's a practice because\nit's not necessarily a thing that you do."},{"time":288440,"text":"It's a process where you have\nto revisit different ways of thinking"},{"time":292240,"text":"for every major decision\nthat you're working on."},{"time":294680,"text":"So I want to go through\nthose three ways of thinking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297960,"text":"So the first: transgenerational thinking."},{"time":301360,"text":"I love the philosophers:"},{"time":303600,"text":"Plato, Socrates, Habermas, Heidegger."},{"time":305440,"text":"I was raised on them."},{"time":308040,"text":"But they all did one thing"},{"time":310000,"text":"that didn't actually seem like a big deal"},{"time":312000,"text":"until I really started\nkind of looking into this."},{"time":314360,"text":"And they all took,"},{"time":316200,"text":"as a unit of measure\nfor their entire reality"},{"time":319120,"text":"of what it meant to be virtuous and good,"},{"time":321880,"text":"the single lifespan,"},{"time":323960,"text":"from birth to death."},{"time":325640,"text":"But here's a problem with these issues:"},{"time":327720,"text":"they stack up on top of us,"},{"time":329160,"text":"because the only way we know\nhow to do something good in the world"},{"time":332320,"text":"is if we do it between\nour birth and our death."},{"time":334560,"text":"That's what we're programmed to do."},{"time":336280,"text":"If you go to the self-help section\nin any bookstore,"},{"time":338760,"text":"it's all about you."},{"time":341400,"text":"Which is great,"},{"time":343280,"text":"unless you're dealing\nwith some of these major issues."},{"time":347960,"text":"And so with transgenerational thinking,"},{"time":351280,"text":"which is really kind of\ntransgenerational ethics,"},{"time":353960,"text":"you're able to expand\nhow you think about these problems,"},{"time":357600,"text":"what is your role\nin helping to solve them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361720,"text":"Now, this isn't something that just has to\nbe done at the Security Council chamber."},{"time":366480,"text":"It's something that you can do\nin a very kind of personal way."},{"time":369760,"text":"So every once in a while, if I'm lucky,\nmy wife and I like to go out to dinner,"},{"time":374200,"text":"and we have three children\nunder the age of seven."},{"time":377480,"text":"So you can imagine\nit's a very peaceful, quiet meal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379933,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":381160,"text":"So we sit down and literally\nall I want to do is just eat and chill,"},{"time":386760,"text":"and my kids have a completely\nand totally different idea"},{"time":389440,"text":"of what we're going to be doing."},{"time":391040,"text":"And so my first idea"},{"time":393400,"text":"is my sandbag strategy, right?"},{"time":395320,"text":"It's to go into my pocket\nand take out the iPhone"},{"time":397680,"text":"and give them \"Frozen\""},{"time":399160,"text":"or some other bestselling game thing."},{"time":403240,"text":"And then I stop"},{"time":406960,"text":"and I have to kind of put on\nthis transgenerational thinking cap."},{"time":411560,"text":"I don't do this in the restaurant,\nbecause it would be bizarre,"},{"time":414560,"text":"but I have to --"},{"time":415880,"text":"I did it once, and that's how\nI learned it was bizarre."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":419560,"text":"And you have to kind of think,\n\"OK, I can do this.\""},{"time":424440,"text":"But what is this teaching them?"},{"time":427480,"text":"So what does it mean\nif I actually bring some paper"},{"time":430120,"text":"or engage with them in conversation?"},{"time":431880,"text":"It's hard. It's not easy,\nand I'm making this very personal."},{"time":434760,"text":"It's actually more traumatic"},{"time":436160,"text":"than some of the big issues\nthat I work on in the world --"},{"time":438920,"text":"entertaining my kids at dinner."},{"time":441560,"text":"But what it does is it connects them\nhere in the present with me,"},{"time":444720,"text":"but it also --"},{"time":446000,"text":"and this is the crux\nof transgenerational thinking ethics --"},{"time":449480,"text":"it sets them up to how they're\ngoing to interact with their kids"},{"time":452800,"text":"and their kids and their kids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456360,"text":"Second, futures thinking."},{"time":458680,"text":"When we think about the future,"},{"time":460680,"text":"10, 15 years out,"},{"time":462920,"text":"give me a vision of what the future is."},{"time":466000,"text":"You don't have to give it to me,\nbut think in your head."},{"time":468680,"text":"And what you're probably going to see"},{"time":470840,"text":"is the dominant cultural lens"},{"time":472680,"text":"that dominates our thinking\nabout the future right now:"},{"time":475760,"text":"technology."},{"time":477840,"text":"So when we think about the problems,"},{"time":479600,"text":"we always put it through\na technological lens,"},{"time":481800,"text":"a tech-centric, a techno-utopia,\nand there's nothing wrong with that,"},{"time":485080,"text":"but it's something that we have to\nreally think deeply about"},{"time":488400,"text":"if we're going to move\non these major issues,"},{"time":491280,"text":"because it wasn't always like this. Right?"},{"time":493360,"text":"The ancients had their way of thinking"},{"time":496840,"text":"about what the future was."},{"time":499640,"text":"The Church definitely had their idea\nof what the future could be,"},{"time":504560,"text":"and you could actually pay your way\ninto that future. Right?"},{"time":507520,"text":"And luckily for humanity,"},{"time":509480,"text":"we got the scientific revolution."},{"time":511640,"text":"From there, we got the technology,"},{"time":513320,"text":"but what has happened --"},{"time":515000,"text":"And by the way, this is not a critique."},{"time":518320,"text":"I love technology."},{"time":520720,"text":"Everything in my house talks back to me,"},{"time":522679,"text":"from my children\nto my speakers to everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":524880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":527720,"text":"But we've abdicated the future\nfrom the high priests in Rome"},{"time":533440,"text":"to the high priests of Silicon Valley."},{"time":537880,"text":"So when we think, well,\nhow are we going to deal with climate"},{"time":541240,"text":"or with poverty or homelessness,"},{"time":542840,"text":"our first reaction is to think about it\nthrough a technology lens."},{"time":547080,"text":"And look, I'm not advocating\nthat we go to this guy."},{"time":551720,"text":"I love Joel, don't get me wrong,"},{"time":554400,"text":"but I'm not saying we go to Joel."},{"time":556080,"text":"What I'm saying is we have to rethink"},{"time":557920,"text":"our base assumption about\nonly looking at the future in one way,"},{"time":562720,"text":"only looking at it\nthrough the dominant lens."},{"time":564880,"text":"Because our problems\nare so big and so vast"},{"time":567080,"text":"that we need to open ourselves up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569920,"text":"So that's why I do everything in my power\nnot to talk about the future."},{"time":574320,"text":"I talk about futures."},{"time":576920,"text":"It opens the conversation again."},{"time":578680,"text":"So when you're sitting and thinking"},{"time":581160,"text":"about how do we move forward\non this major issue --"},{"time":584360,"text":"it could be at home,"},{"time":585920,"text":"it could be at work,"},{"time":587920,"text":"it could be again on the global stage --"},{"time":590800,"text":"don't cut yourself off from thinking\nabout something beyond technology as a fix"},{"time":595240,"text":"because we're more concerned\nabout technological evolution right now"},{"time":598800,"text":"than we are about moral evolution."},{"time":600960,"text":"And unless we fix for that,"},{"time":603000,"text":"we're not going to be able\nto get out of short-termism"},{"time":605600,"text":"and get to where we want to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":607440,"text":"The final, telos thinking.\nThis comes from the Greek root."},{"time":610680,"text":"Ultimate aim and ultimate purpose."},{"time":612960,"text":"And it's really asking one question:"},{"time":616120,"text":"to what end?"},{"time":618280,"text":"When was the last time\nyou asked yourself: To what end?"},{"time":621320,"text":"And when you asked yourself that,\nhow far out did you go?"},{"time":625640,"text":"Because long isn't long enough anymore."},{"time":629560,"text":"Three, five years doesn't cut it."},{"time":631480,"text":"It's 30, 40, 50, 100 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634800,"text":"In Homer's epic, \"The Odyssey,\""},{"time":637040,"text":"Odysseus had the answer to his \"what end.\""},{"time":640120,"text":"It was Ithaca."},{"time":641880,"text":"It was this bold vision\nof what he wanted --"},{"time":644000,"text":"to return to Penelope."},{"time":645400,"text":"And I can tell you,\nbecause of the work that I'm doing,"},{"time":648040,"text":"but also you know it intuitively --\nwe have lost our Ithaca."},{"time":650920,"text":"We have lost our \"to what end,\"\nso we stay on this hamster wheel."},{"time":654480,"text":"And yes, we're trying\nto solve these problems,"},{"time":656680,"text":"but what comes after we solve the problem?"},{"time":660160,"text":"And unless you define what comes after,\npeople aren't going to move."},{"time":664400,"text":"The businesses --\nthis isn't just about business --"},{"time":666840,"text":"but the businesses that do consistently,\nwho break out of short-termism"},{"time":670200,"text":"not surprisingly\nare family-run businesses."},{"time":672240,"text":"They're transgenerational. They're telos.\nThey think about the futures."},{"time":675840,"text":"And this is an ad for Patek Philippe.\nThey're 175 years old,"},{"time":679560,"text":"and what's amazing\nis that they literally embody"},{"time":682640,"text":"this kind of longpathian sense\nin their brand,"},{"time":685480,"text":"because, by the way,\nyou never actually own a Patek Philippe,"},{"time":688400,"text":"and I definitely won't --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":690000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":691040,"text":"unless somebody wants to just\nthrow 25,000 dollars on the stage."},{"time":694064,"text":"You merely look after it\nfor the next generation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698840,"text":"So it's important that we remember,"},{"time":701320,"text":"the future, we treat it like a noun."},{"time":704480,"text":"It's not. It's a verb."},{"time":706760,"text":"It requires action."},{"time":708040,"text":"It requires us to push into it."},{"time":709880,"text":"It's not this thing that washes over us."},{"time":711840,"text":"It's something that we\nactually have total control over."},{"time":714520,"text":"But in a short-term society,\nwe end up feeling like we don't."},{"time":717440,"text":"We feel like we're trapped."},{"time":718800,"text":"We can push through that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":722000,"text":"Now I'm getting more comfortable"},{"time":725200,"text":"in the fact that at some point"},{"time":728360,"text":"in the inevitable future,"},{"time":731000,"text":"I will die."},{"time":733240,"text":"But because of these new ways\nof thinking and doing,"},{"time":737360,"text":"both in the outside world\nand also with my family at home,"},{"time":741320,"text":"and what I'm leaving my kids,\nI get more comfortable in that fact."},{"time":744480,"text":"And it's something that a lot of us\nare really uncomfortable with,"},{"time":747640,"text":"but I'm telling you,"},{"time":749840,"text":"think it through."},{"time":751280,"text":"Apply this type of thinking\nand you can push yourself past"},{"time":754040,"text":"what's inevitably\nvery, very uncomfortable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756120,"text":"And it all begins really\nwith yourself asking this question:"},{"time":760840,"text":"What is your longpath?"},{"time":763880,"text":"But I ask you, when you ask yourself that"},{"time":766800,"text":"now or tonight or behind a steering wheel"},{"time":769080,"text":"or in the boardroom or the situation room:"},{"time":774320,"text":"push past the longpath,"},{"time":776520,"text":"quick, oh, what's my longpath\nthe next three years or five years?"},{"time":779840,"text":"Try and push past your own life if you can"},{"time":783480,"text":"because it makes you do things\na little bit bigger"},{"time":785880,"text":"than you thought were possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":788800,"text":"Yes, we have huge,\nhuge problems out there."},{"time":793800,"text":"With this process, with this thinking,"},{"time":797120,"text":"I think we can make a difference."},{"time":799240,"text":"I think you can make a difference,"},{"time":801800,"text":"and I believe in you guys."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803440,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804680,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}